BarChartWidget.description:
Use a bar chart to display a series of bars, each with a discrete x value and a continuous y value. eg:
{
    "type": "bar-chart",
    "data": [
        {"x": "A", "y": 10},
        {"x": "B", "y": 20},
        {"x": "C", "y": 25},
    ]
}

DescriptionWidget.description:
A description widget. Use a description to display a summary description at the top of a page or section. eg:
{
    "type": "description",
    "description": "Some description text"
}

HorizontalRulerWidget.description:
A horizontal ruler widget. Use a horizontal ruler to separate sections of a page. eg:
{
    "type": "horizontal-ruler"
}

LineChartWidget.description:
Use a line chart to display a series of lines, each with a label and a series of data. X values can be either continuous or discrete. 
Example:
    {"type": "line-chart", "datasets": [
        {
            "label": "A",
            "data": [
                {"x": "A", "y": 10},
                {"x": "B", "y": 20},
                {"x": "C", "y": 25},
            ],
        }]
    }

MetricWidget.description:
Use a metric to display a single value, with optional sentiment. eg:
{
    "type": "metric",
    "data": {
        "data_type": "number",
        "value": 10
    }
}

PieChartWidget.description:
A pie chart widget. Use a pie chart to display a series of slices, each with a label and a value. Values must be postive.
For best results, a pie chart should have at most 5 slices. eg:
{ 
    "type": "pie-chart",
    "data": [
        {"label": "A", "value": 10},
        {"label": "B", "value": 20},
        {"label": "C", "value": 25},
    ]
}

ScatterChartWidget.description:
Use a scatter chart to display a series of data, each with a label and a series of points. X and Y values are continuous. eg:
{
    "type": "scatter-chart",
    "datasets": [
        {
            "label": "A",
            "data": [
                {"x": 1, "y": 10},
                {"x": 2, "y": 20},
                {"x": 3, "y": 25}
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "B",
            "data": [
                {"x": 1.2, "y": 15},
                {"x": 2.8, "y": 25},
                {"x": 3.14, "y": 30}
            ]
        }
    ]
}

TableWidget.description:
Use a table to display tabular data. eg:
{
    "type": "table",
    "columns": [
        {
            "name": "Column 1",
            "data_key": "col1",
        },
        {
            "name": "Column 2",
            "data_key": "col2",
        }
    ],
    "rows": [
        {"col1": "Alice", "col2": 25},
        {"col1": "Bob", "col2": 30}
    ]
}

TitleWidget.description:
A title widget. Use a title to display a summary title at the top of a page or section. eg:
{
    "type": "title",
    "title": "Title Text"
}

VerticalRulerWidget.description:
A vertical ruler widget. Use a vertical ruler to separate sections of a page. eg:
{
    "type": "vertical-ruler"
}

